    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The Lenape Indians made winter homes inland but spent summers on Barnegat’s shores, gathering clams and crafting wampum from shells.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        22,
        23
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.barnegat.net/about-barnegat/history-of-barnegat/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "White settlers first arrived around 1720, and by 1750 several families had established homes near the creeks and bays.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        25,
        26
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.barnegat.net/about-barnegat/history-of-barnegat/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Barnegat once hosted two railroad depots: the Tuckerton RR on Memorial Drive and the Central RR on West Bay Avenue.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
